WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.000
What does it take to find the right flatmate in
a city like Bangalore?

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:20.000
360 FlatMates is a Flutter mobile app built to
solve exactly that problem.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:28.000
Connecting people through compatible
living arrangements.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:38.000
Users can browse listings, swipe through
potential flatmates based on lifestyle compatibility,

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:45.000
chat in real time, and schedule property visits.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:55.000
It turns the often chaotic process of finding a
flatmate into something structured and human.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:01:05.000
The tech stack is modern Flutter with Riverpod
for state management, GoRouter for navigation,

00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:12.000
Supabase for authentication, and a Dio-based
networking layer connecting to a FastAPI backend.

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:22.000
On startup, the app initializes Firebase,
Supabase, and local storage through a ProviderScope.

00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:32.000
The router checks authentication status and routes
users to login, onboarding, or the home feed.

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:42.000
The home feed shows listings as horizontal cards
with a search bar and filter chips.

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:50.000
The Swipe feature uses a card deck with
compatibility scoring.

00:01:50.000 --> 00:02:00.000
The Chat system uses Supabase realtime for live
messages with an SSE fallback.

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:10.000
Property owners use a seven step wizard to
list their flats.

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:20.000
Interested users can schedule visits through a
calendar picker with time slots.

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:26.000
A terracotta accent anchors the palette with
paper and ink scales for backgrounds and text.

00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:35.000
Three palette options plus full dark mode support.

00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:45.000
A server-sent events service maintains a persistent
connection to the backend.

00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:55.000
When events arrive like a new match or new message,
the event router invalidates Riverpod providers.

00:02:55.000 --> 00:03:05.000
The architecture follows a feature-first pattern.
Each feature has its own controller and pages.

00:03:05.000 --> 00:03:12.000
Business logic lives in controllers, not widgets.

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:22.000
The codebase has about 70,000 lines of Dart across
14 feature modules and 18 reusable widgets.

00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:32.000
Localization available in English and Hindi.

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:47.000
This covers the key parts: product purpose, tech
stack, startup flow, features, design system,
realtime infrastructure, and architecture layers.

00:03:47.000 --> 00:04:00.000
The full documentation is available in the wiki.
